Remove X
Send Feedback
Given a string, compute recursively a new string where all 'x' chars have been removed.
Input format :
String S
Output format :
Modified String
Constraints :
1 <= |S| <= 10^3
where |S| represents the length of string S. 
Sample Input 1 :
xaxb
Sample Output 1:
ab
Sample Input 2 :
abc
Sample Output 2:
abc
Sample Input 3 :
xx
Sample Output 3:

Code:

// Change in the given string itself. So no need to return or print anything
#include<cstring>
void removeX(char input[]) {
    // Write your code here
	if(strlen(input)==0){
        return;
    }
    if(input[0]=='x'){
        for(int i=0;i<strlen(input);i++){
            input[i]=input[i+1];
        }
        removeX(input);
    }
    else{
        removeX(input+1);
    }
}
